<Base title="Principles — Harasyn.co" topbarVariant="page">
  <div class="text-page-title">
    <h1 class="text_quote">Principals</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="text-intro">In the 1970's Dieter Rams asked himself, "What is good design?" in an effort to combat, in part "impenetrable confusion of forms."<sup style="font-size: .6rem; font-weight: bolder; color: #FE4902">1</sup> As a contributor to the vast and expanding universe of digital experiences, I've asked the same question and framed the driving factors behind my approach.</div>

  <div class="principals">
    <div class="principals-content">
      <a>Focus</a>
      <p class="text">A product must have a clear objective. Every component – no matter how small – must know what role it plays and how it supports the larger system.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="principals">
    <div class="principals-content">
      <a>Comprehension</a>
      <p class="text">A product, and the elements within, must be self contained and perceptible. Usage and interaction should be easily understood and expected.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="principals">
    <div class="principals-content">
      <a>Balance</a>
      <p class="text">A product must be proportioned to its purpose. Elements – technical or otherwise – should work in harmony and bear the appropriate amount of weight.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="principals">
    <div class="principals-content">
      <a>Congruity</a>
      <p class="text">A product must be appropriate in form and function to its ecosystem. Usage should match environmental and behavioral expectations.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="principals">
    <div class="principals-content">
      <a>Resilience</a>
      <p class="text">A product must be structured to adapt and evolve. Form and function should be structured to accept shifts in environment and behavior.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="principals">
    <div class="principals-content">
      <a>Integrity</a>
      <p class="text">A product must be principled in purpose and execution. Details should never be overlooked and proven methods of craft should be considered.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="principals">
    <div class="principals-content">
      <a>Joy</a>
      <p class="text">A product must elicit joy – either in direct use or from the outcome it creates. Form and function should be rooted in an empathic understanding of the user.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="principals-license">
    <p><sup style="font-size: .6rem; font-weight: bolder; color: #FE4902">1</sup>This work references <a href="https://www.vitsoe.com/us/about/good-design" target="_blank">Creative Commons Dieter Rams: ten principles for good design" by Dieter Rams</a>, used under CC-BY-NC-ND 3.0.</p>
  </div>
</Base>
